So, it was really clean,, until you shoot it and the gunpowder ruins it. Honestly, I shot it 3 times and I've gotten tired of cleaning it,,, plus I've gotten into a new hobby which don't allow me time at the shooting range anymore. So, getting rid of all my guns starting with the one's I can do without 1st. Asking $700 but will accept a fair and reasonable offer.

title: For Sale:  FEG FP9 – NIB; 9mm Pistol; Browning High Power Clone
postcontent: New in Box. Mint condition. New, reduced price!Pistol is in its original box, with an extra 13-round magazine, manual, and cleaning rod. All original parts included. Factory walnut grips, fixed sights, and the rare vented rib. Made in Hungary by FEG. After the original Browning patents for the Browning Hi-Power (BHP) expired, the Hungarian conglomerate of FÉG developed one of the most faithful versions of the Browning design ever made in quantity outside the FN factories in Belgium and Portugal. The BHP and the FP9 are so similar that many parts are interchangeable between them, including the magazines. So, like the BHP, the Fp9 is a single action pistol. This pistol feels great in the hand – exactly like my 1981 BHP - and has a similar trigger pull. Note: the non-vented rib version of this pistol was exported as PJK-9HP/P9M models.
